The Commissioner for Water Resources in Kano State, Sadiq Aminu Wali, has resigned from the state’s executive council. The Commissioner in a statement explained that he resigned to seek other opportunities in his political career in the preparations for the 2023 general elections on the platform of the All Progressives Congress (APC).
Sadiq Aminu Wali did not disclose what election ticket he will be seeking next; he, however, assured Governor Abdullahi Ganduje of his unflinching loyalty and support in the governor’s leadership of the state APC.
